<div class = "overview-letter-body">
  <p class = "overview-letter-body-p">It is with great pleasure that Model UN at UC San Diego presents the first ever San Diego Intercollegiate Model United Nations, SANDIMUN I. After months of preparation with our Model United Nations team, we are honored to finally present to you the highly anticipated conference of SANDIMUN I!</p>

<p class = "overview-letter-body-p">As Secretary General of SANDIMUN I, I look forward to the three days of vigorous debate and well-tempered diplomacy. I have always wanted to continue my college Model United Nations career by creating a conference of my own, with the participation of other college students. Being given the honor of becoming the Secretary General in a distinguished conference, such as SANDIMUN, has always been my dream. This year, SANDIMUN has been able to diversify and progress with the participation of more universities. It is difficult for me to put in words what a privilege it is to witness fellow college students coming together from different places, to resolve current issues, and propose novel solutions to the issues facing the world.</p>

<p class = "overview-letter-body-p">This year, SANDIMUN will be encompassing a total of five different committees - the Historical United Nations Security Council, Committee of International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA), Special Session of the General Assembly: Security Council Reform, United Nations Office on Drugs and Crime (UNODC) and last but not least, Joint Crisis Committee: 2016 Presidential Election. Delegates will be able to engage in heated debates on relevant issues ranging from crypto currencies in the global marketplace, to reforming the United Nations Security Council.</p>

<p class = "overview-letter-body-p">As SANDIMUN takes its next step toward a new level of success, we hope delegates will seize this unique opportunity to participate in active debates, aiming to solve the pressing issues of our time.  We hope and anticipate that this conference will be a chance for delegates to improve themselves as human beings, as well as the condition of their fellow man.  I look forward to seeing you all at the conference.</p>

<p class = "overview-letter-end-p">Sincerely,</p>
<p class = "overview-letter-end-p">Emily Lu <br />
Secretary General (UCSD Class of 2017)</p>
